        "id": 5085
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-01-21T14:21:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I thought we had a rule about not allowing bottom-left with fully lazy proxies. I think we should. You can\u0027t reason about absolute rectangles for things like copies and uploads for bottom left if you don\u0027t know the size. Coincidentally I\u0027m working on making a task for write pixels and as part of that am removing the view from task targets.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 69,
        "startChar": 11,
        "endLine": 69,
        "endChar": 65
      },
      "revId": "5d2f9ec7386240c38d457bfe2fc6a0e492325c9b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b6b511fd_7990a1eb",
        "filename": "gm/lazytiling.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 19
      },
      "lineNbr": 69,
      "author": {
        "id": 5230
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-01-21T17:15:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "As discussed off-line, in this instance the fullyLazy proxy is just a stand-in for a \"DDL target\"-proxy which, in the offset-draw case, knows its recording width \u0026 height but not the width \u0026 height of the target into which it will finally be drawn. I will follow up and determine if Chrome can live with only TopLeft DDL targets.\n\nAdditionally, once the \"DDL target\"-proxy concept is exposed I will follow up on this CL and switch it over to using that type of proxy.",
      "parentUuid": "34840831_5c93adb2",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 69,
        "startChar": 11,
        "endLine": 69,
        "endChar": 65
      },
      "revId": "5d2f9ec7386240c38d457bfe2fc6a0e492325c9b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
